did.abstract: Records of the United Workers Union-Independent and its precursor organization, the Staff Rights Organizing Committee of the University of Washington

bioghist.p: Records of the Staff Rights Organizing Committee (SROC) and United Workers Union-Independent (UWU-I). SROC mobilized University of Washington staff to fight a discriminatory job reclassification that resulted in the first strike at the University of Washington in 1973. After the strike, members of the organizing committee formed their own union, United Workers Union-Independent. The union raised issues about the effects of racism and sexism on salaries that later became the concept of the Comparable Worth campaign. UWU-I's advocacy for the lowest-paid, unorganized women and people of color on campus prodded other campus unions to better represent these workers.

scopecontent.p: Records of the United Workers Union-Independent and its precursor organization, the Staff Rights Organizing Committee of the University of Washington. Includes photos, buttons, newsletters, leaflets, and press releases.

phystech.p: Records stored offsite; advanced arrangements are necessary. Please contact us for more information.

userestrict.p: The creators' literary rights have been transferred to the University of Washington Libraries.
